<br>
1. I would suggest Vincent (or one of the officers) to maybe copy Worst post into another post titled &quot;recruiting policies&quot; or something.  I think he has two good issues  and it may get confusing if people start discussing both of them in this one post.<br>
<br>
2. DD, you bring up a good point.  I actually believe this issue was raised in EQ, and was voted on by the membership or at least discussed.  The way &quot;I&quot; remember it was:<br>
<br>
The procedure for officers was as it is now for us in DAOC: &quot;officers nominate a canidate to fill a position and the general membership votes if they would like this person as an officer&quot;.<br>
<br>
People suggested, why don't we the membership nominate and vote on who should fill that position, and officers will get a single vote as being a member.<br>
<br>
I believe your suggestion is &quot;somewhat&quot; similar to the last.  I believe it was suggested in EQ for the same reason you posted yours (tell me if I'm wrong), in that some of the general membership felt that they were not part of the officer nomination process.  Which is a very valid point.<br>
<br>
I believe the main reason the people who were for the original (our current) system were for it was, because they felt the current officers had the best idea of:<br>
<br>
1. What it took to be an officer<br>
2. What was needed at the time for the SD officer group, meaning who was the best person for the role that needed to be filled.<br>
<br>
Also a worry about people nominating people for positions was will it become a popularity contest?  Will feelings get hurt if they are not nominated?<br>
<br>
I don't know what the right answer is (if there is one), I just bring this up, not to you but to the guild since we may be able to learn from what we have done in the past.  I am very glad as everyone else is that you brought this up.  I agree if people aren't willing to speak their minds then we will have a hard rough road.  Again what I stated above is what I remember (could be way off) from EQ, and that doesn't mean its right for us. <br>
<br>
/ramble off<br>
/work on<br>
<br>
Ezekiell <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=519.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=519.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=519.topic&index=13><img src=http://werzat.freeservers.com/add.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=519.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm1.threadControl?topicID=519.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=519.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=519.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub15.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="daggersincamelotfrm24">General<option value="daggersincamelotfrm1">DAoC General<option value="daggersincamelotfrm2">Events<option value="daggersincamelotfrm27">War Room<option value="daggersincamelotfrm4">Trade Skills<option value="daggersincamelotfrm5">Treasury